## Summary

Refactored all sensor interfaces (`ICompass`, `IGyroscope`, `IAccelerometer`, `IMagnetometer`, `IBarometer`) to implement `ISensor` and `IDeviceCapabilities` explicitly rather than through inheritance. This preserves backward compatibility for libraries built with net8/net9 while enabling explicit interface usage for the new hierarchy pattern.

## Changes Made

### Before
```csharp
public interface ICompass : ISensor
{
    void Start(SensorSpeed sensorSpeed, bool applyLowPassFilter);
    event EventHandler<CompassChangedEventArgs> ReadingChanged;
}
```

### After
```csharp
public interface ICompass
{
    // Public members for backward compatibility
    bool IsSupported { get; }
    bool IsMonitoring { get; }
    void Start(SensorSpeed sensorSpeed);
    void Start(SensorSpeed sensorSpeed, bool applyLowPassFilter);
    void Stop();
    event EventHandler<CompassChangedEventArgs> ReadingChanged;
}

partial class CompassImplementation : ICompass, ISensor, IDeviceCapabilities
{
    // Explicit interface implementations that delegate to public members
    bool ISensor.IsMonitoring => IsMonitoring;
    void ISensor.Start(SensorSpeed sensorSpeed) => Start(sensorSpeed);
    void ISensor.Stop() => Stop();
    bool IDeviceCapabilities.IsSupported => IsSupported;
}
```

## Benefits

1. **Backward Compatibility**: All existing public members (`IsSupported`, `IsMonitoring`, `Start`, `Stop`) remain as public members of each interface
2. **Explicit Interface Support**: New code can use explicit interface casting for the `ISensor`/`IDeviceCapabilities` hierarchy
3. **Delegation Pattern**: Explicit interface implementations delegate to the public members, ensuring consistent behavior

